The paper deals with the power flow equations, which are fundamental in power systems planning and operations. The approach is based on the theory of monotone operators and related algorithms for solving variational inequalities involving monotone operators. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of solving the power flow equations, which may fall under the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The paper also introduces a family of convex domains characterized by Linear Matrix Inequalities, which may fall under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper may also belong to the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category, as it deals with computational methods for solving power flow equations. Finally, the paper may belong to the cs.ETM (Emerging Technologies) sub-category, as it discusses a new approach for solving power flow equations.
